@node "Author" "About the author"
@next "Main"
@prev "Copyright"
Hello.  My name is Tristan R. Young, and I've been working with computers for 17 years.
Starting with a TRS-80 COCO 2, worked my way down to an Intel 386, then back up to the
machine which gave Billy G. pleanty of ideas to rip off - The Amiga.

I'm 25 years old (12/27/72) living in Ottawa, Ontario, Canada.  After a long day at
work trying to debug Windows NT 4.0 crashes, I look forward to returning home to my
Amiga 3000.

My future goals include integrating an Amiga into my Honda, educating the less
fortunate (Intel-compatible owners), and to open the best dance-bar this side of the
milky way.

A computer technician by trade, I've devoted much of my focus to Astronomy, which
computers play an active part.  Learning the latest technology and applying it is what
I'm all about.

Ok, this is boring, so go read something else.

Oh, one more thing.  If you need to reach me, EMail:  tyoung@netrover.com
@endnode

