<SARCASM>

        3.  Bitch and complain about how badly an install script is needed.  :)

</SARCASM>
@endnode

@node "Usage" "How to use a script"
@next "Thanks"
@prev "Installation"

 @{b}@{u}Voyager@{ub}@{uu}

        1.  Load Voyager
        2.  Open your General Config menu item
        3.  Select the MAIL/NEWS submenu
        4.  For the MAIL editor, cycle through to "EXTERNAL"
        5.  In the textbox beside the cyclegadget, enter:

                dh1:rexxc/rx dh1:scripts/yam.rexx %t %s

        6.  Edit the YAM.REXX script and set your path for YAM.


        * note *  don't change the order of the "%t %s".
        * note *  Voyager doesn't seem to clone the path, so pointing
                  specifically to the RX program is neccessary.

 @{b}@{u}YAM@{ub}@{uu}

        1.  Load YAM
        2.  Open your Configuration menu item
        3.  Select the AREXX submenu
        4.  Select "When double-clicking an URL", and set it up as:

                Cyclegadget:  AREXX
                     Script:  dh1:scripts/gotourl.rexx
        Open console window:  no checkmark
       Wait for termination:  no checkmark

        5.  Edit the GOTOURL.REXX script and set your path for Voyager.
@endnode

